1. The Spectral Principle

Across science there’s a recurring discovery:

You understand a system by examining its spectrum.

Meaning:
Instead of looking at the object itself, you look at the frequencies, eigenvalues, or resonances it produces.

Examples:

System	Spectrum
violin string	harmonics
molecule	energy levels
graph network	eigenvalues
signals	Fourier frequencies
integers	zeta zeros

So the pattern becomes:

structure → vibration → spectrum → insight

This is one of the most universal analytic tricks humanity has discovered.

